{
  "stem": "13584.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But this I don't remember exactly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My mother told me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PHONE RINGING]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Throughout her life.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some-- most of them, I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some, I, I, I do remember.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It, it's a love song, and I think from the city where she came from.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There is a little house standing in a small, small street.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And over there, on the attic apartment, lives [NON-ENGLISH], my girl.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And every evening, I'm, I'm in front of her house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I'm whistling for her to come down, but her mother says not to respond.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's not nice to whistle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It doesn't fit to a Jewish boy to whistle.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH] sewed for me a, a little sack for the, for the prayer book and [NON-ENGLISH] with the [?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Mark of ?] David on it, especially for him as a gift.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he listens to her, the small feet, how they're, they are running down the stairs to see him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But then, all of a sudden, oh, god, the boy says, it was just a dream.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was a sweet dream.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There was some-- so many songs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH], which is very popular songs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They are songs who I cannot sing and I cannot even repeat it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were songs who were not recorded anywhere.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were even songs created after Hitler came to power, creating Yiddish songs that-- a song in Yiddish, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], the Jews lived a good life before Hitler came to power.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And this was-- my mother used to tell me, this was, was, was singing a Jewish beggar, a blind man who came to the yard and was singing this.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Apparently, he was a refugee from Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember this, but my mother used to sing this.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were many songs, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
